# frontend-architecture

## Component Hierarchy

### Game Interface (90/100)
`frontend/src/components/game/GameInterface.tsx`
- Centralizes game state management for turn phases, player resources, and momentum
- Orchestrates interactions between battlefield, card hands, and player HUDs
- Manages turn-based gameplay flow and resource resets

### Battlefield Management (85/100)
`frontend/src/features/battlefield/Battlefield.tsx`
- Implements grid-based unit placement system
- Controls player and enemy zone interactions
- Handles battlefield state updates during gameplay phases

### Card Management (80/100)
`frontend/src/features/cards/CardHand.tsx`
- Controls card selection mechanics based on energy availability
- Manages player hand states and card playability rules
- Implements energy cost validation for card plays

### Turn Phase System (75/100)
`frontend/src/features/battlefield/TurnManager.tsx`
- Defines turn phases (DEPLOY, ACTION, END)
- Controls phase transitions and associated game state changes
- Implements turn timer functionality

### Player Information Display (70/100)
`frontend/src/features/players/PlayerHUD.tsx`
- Visualizes player and opponent stats using circular progress indicators
- Updates resource displays (health, momentum, energy)
- Highlights active player status

### Opponent Hand Visualization (65/100)
`frontend/src/features/players/OpponentHand.tsx`
- Displays opponent card count and hand size
- Implements face-down card visualization
- Manages opponent hand animations

## State Management
- Centralizes game state in GameInterface component
- Implements resource management for energy, health, and momentum
- Controls turn-based state transitions
- Manages battlefield grid state and unit positions

